cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper deals with the problem of label noise in deep learning, which is a common issue in computer vision and natural language processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper proposes an improved mean absolute error (IMAE) loss function, which is a modification of the traditional MAE loss function. This makes it relevant to the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as well.
